xercise-4/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 12:48:57 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_updated.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-4/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Unified memory</title> <description>&lt;p&gt;Unified memory streamlines the data transfer process between the host (CPU) and the device (GPU), minimizing the need for explicit data movement by programme...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-5/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 12:48:57 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_updated.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-5/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Preparation</title> <description>&lt;h4&gt;1. &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.lxp.lu/first-steps/quick_start/&#34;&gt;How to login to the MeluXina machine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;1.1 [Please take a look if you are using Windows](https://docs...&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/preparation/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 12:48:57 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_updated.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/preparation/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Profiling and performance</title> <description>&lt;h3&gt;Time measurement&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;In CUDA, the execution time can be measured by using the CUDA events. CUDA API events shall be created using &lt;code&gt;cudaEvent_t&lt;/code&gt;, for example...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/profiling/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026